@description.body: Transports requests to a server using dynamic script tags. This class should not be used directly by client programmers. NOTE: Instances of this class must be disposed of after use

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Switches the readystate by setting the internal state.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Sets a request header with the given value. This method is not implemented at the moment.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the value of the given response header. This method is not implemented at the moment and returns always "null".

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Provides an hash of all response headers. This method is not implemented at the moment and returns an empty map.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the current status code of the request if available or -1 if not. This method needs implementation (returns always 200).

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Provides the status text for the current request if available and null otherwise. This method needs implementation (returns always an empty string)

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the length of the content as fetched thus far. This method needs implementation (returns always 0).

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the content of the response.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {null | String} If successful content of response as string.
@return.description: If successful content of response as string.
